      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "They dwelt in Gilead — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That is, the children or tribe of Gad inhabited a part of Gilead, the Reubenites and Manassites dwelling in other parts of it, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 3:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "In Bashan — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "In the land of Bashan, as is said, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 5:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And in her towns — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "In some of her cities and towns. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "In all the suburbs of Sharon — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Not that Sharon in Canaan, but that to the east of Jordan, namely, in the fields and pasture-grounds of it. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Upon their borders — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The borders of Gilead and Bashan. For Gilead, properly so called, or the greatest part of it, belonged to the Reubenites, and the greatest part of Bashan to the Manassites; and the Gadites, whose habitation was between these two tribes, had those parts of both these countries which lay toward their borders.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
