  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The families descended from Buz \"dwelt in Gilead,\" in the part of that district lying to the south of the Jabbok, which Moses had given to the Gadites and Reubenites (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 3:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); \"In Bashan and her daughters,\" that is, in the villages belonging to the cities of Bashan and Gilead inhabited by them (for the suffix in בּבנותיה is to be referred distributively to both districts, or the cities in them). \"And in all the pasture grounds (מגרשׁ, cf. on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 35:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") of Sharon unto their outgoings.\" שׁרון, Sharon, lay not in Perea, but is a great plain on the shore of the Mediterranean Sea, extending from Carmel to near Joppa, famed for its great fertility and its rich growth of flowers (Sol 2:1; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 33:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
